President Trump made several remarks during a press conference on October 22, 2018. He expressed concern about the group of migrants traveling to the United States and stated that the countries of Guatemala, Honduras, and El Salvador have not done enough to stop them. He also mentioned his conversations with the leaders of Saudi Arabia and Turkey regarding the disappearance of journalist Jamal Khashoggi, stating that he is not satisfied with the information he has received so far. Additionally, he discussed his support for Senator Ted Cruz in the Texas Senate race and his plans to introduce a middle-income tax reduction. The President also commented on the upcoming midterm elections, the issue of sanctuary cities in California, and the potential increase in the U.S. nuclear arsenal.